        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 16 at 6:47PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 647 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Crawford, or 20 miles northeast of Montrose, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Crawford and Maher.

This includes Colorado 92 between mile markers 24 and 38.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
